This paper deals with statistical data-to-text generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper focuses on using large-scale datasets with loosely aligned data and text pairs, which is a common problem in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses multi-instance learning and encoder-decoder architecture, which are common techniques in machine learning (ML). Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with discovering correspondences between data and text pairs, which is a task related to information retrieval (IR). Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses DBPedia facts, which is a structured data source, and deals with content selection, which is a task related to data management. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.DB (Databases).
